// AnnotationComponents
// Low-level UI building blocks for the annotation system used inside the
// CodeMirror editor. Provides the widget DOM element, a React popover for
// creating/editing annotations, and an inline annotation display component.

FUNCTION AnnotationWidget(annotation, onClick) -> HTMLElement
  Creates a span DOM element styled as a colored dot for the annotation type
  (comment/propose/approve/reject). Attaches a click listener that calls onClick
  with the annotation index. Returns the element for use as a CodeMirror widget.

---

FUNCTION AnnotationPopover(annotation, position, onSave, onDelete, onClose) -> JSX  EXPORT
  Inline popover rendered near a clicked annotation dot.
  Shows a textarea pre-filled with annotation text, type selector buttons,
  Save and Delete buttons, and an X close button.
  Closes on Escape key or click outside.

---

FUNCTION InlineAnnotationView(annotation, index, onSave, onDelete) -> JSX  EXPORT
  Compact inline display of a single annotation below a code line.
  Shows annotation type badge, text, and edit/delete icon buttons.
  Clicking edit enters an inline edit mode with a textarea.
